textBeforeTable: As It Stood Table Manager: Nigel Adkins Unused substitutes: Taylor, Pearce, Harte, Hunt Line-up: McCarthy; Gunter, Morrison, Mariappa, Kelly; Robson-Kanu (Carrico 82'), Guthrie, Karacan, McCleary; McAnuff (Blackman 73'); Pogrebnyak (Le Fondre 72') Reading Manager: Martin Jol Unused substitutes: Etheridge, Hughes, Manolev, Frimpong Line-up: Schwarzer; Riether, Senderos, Hangeland, John Arne Riise (Richardson 56'); Duff (Kacaniklic 71'), Karagounis (Rodallega 28'), Enoh, Emanuelson; Ruiz; Berbatov Fulham Referee: Neil Swarbrick Venue: Craven Cottage, London Attendance: 24,087 Date: Saturday 4 May 2013 Kick-off: 3:00pm Competition: Barclays Premier League Match Information The Whites were undone, though, as Karacan added a fourth as the game moved into the last 10 minutes. The ball wasn’t cleared in the Fulham box and the midfielder arrived to power a low shot into the bottom corner. Ruiz tried to net his hat-trick and spur another comeback, but his free-kick was hit over the bar and then Rodallega came within an inch of scoring in the last minute but was just unable to get his head on the cross.
